                            <comment id="13058877" author="stack" created="Fri, 1 Jul 2011 23:55:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HRegionInfo no longer carries an HTableDescriptor instance in TRUNK.  Will that fix it Dave?  In branch there is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3906&quot; title=&quot;When HMaster is running,there are a lot of RegionLoad instances&#65288;far greater than the regions&#65289;,it has risk of OOME.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3906&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3906&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  Does that help?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13058887" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 2 Jul 2011 00:41:23 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;HRegionInfo no longer carries an HTableDescriptor instance in TRUNK&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe we should do this in 0.90 too? ... assuming we do the right thing with actually returning valid HTDs from methods as if nothing has changed behind the curtain.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13060001" author="davelatham" created="Tue, 5 Jul 2011 16:58:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, that should probably do it, Stack.  Thanks for the work.  Sorry for the duplicate issue.&lt;/p&gt;

